# The CSS Box Model

Every single element on a webpage — every heading, paragraph, image, button — is a rectangular box. CSS treats them all this way. The **box model** describes how that box is structured from the inside out:

```
┌─────────────────────────────┐  ← margin (outside the border)
│  ┌───────────────────────┐  │  ← border
│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  │  │  ← padding (inside the border)
│  │  │    CONTENT      │  │  │
│  │  └─────────────────┘  │  │
│  └───────────────────────┘  │
└─────────────────────────────┘
```

- **Content** — the actual text, image, or child elements
- **Padding** — transparent space between the content and the border
- **Border** — the line around the padding and content
- **Margin** — transparent space outside the border, pushing other elements away

## Setting Each Layer

```css
.box {
  /* Content size */
  width: 300px;
  height: 150px;

  /* Padding — inside the border */
  padding: 16px;               /* all four sides */
  padding: 8px 16px;           /* top/bottom  left/right */
  padding: 4px 8px 12px 16px;  /* top right bottom left (clockwise) */

  /* Border */
  border: 2px solid #22c55e;
  border-radius: 8px;

  /* Margin — outside the border */
  margin: 24px;
  margin: 0 auto;  /* centre horizontally */
}
```

## box-sizing: border-box

By default, `width` and `height` apply only to the content area. Padding and border add to the total size:

```css
/* Default (content-box): width=300 + 32px padding + 4px border = 336px total */
.box { width: 300px; padding: 16px; border: 2px solid; }

/* border-box: total stays 300px — padding and border go INSIDE */
* { box-sizing: border-box; }
.box { width: 300px; padding: 16px; border: 2px solid; }
```

Adding `* { box-sizing: border-box; }` to every project makes sizing predictable. It is the first rule in almost every professional CSS file.

## display Property

Each element has a default `display` value:

- `block` — takes the full width, starts on a new line (`div`, `p`, `h1`)
- `inline` — flows with text, no width/height control (`span`, `a`, `em`)
- `inline-block` — flows with text but accepts width/height
- `none` — hides the element completely (removed from layout)

